sql:
SELECT m.meter_id, m.meter_type, m.equipment_identifier, m.firmware_version, m.hardware_version, m.manufacturer, m.model
FROM meters m
WHERE m.meter_id NOT IN (
  SELECT mt.meter_id FROM meter_tariffs mt
);

SELECT SUM(CAST(REPLACE(value, 'kWh', '') AS REAL)) AS total_energy_consumed
FROM meter_data
WHERE attribute = 'Meter Energy Consumption'
AND meter_id IN (
  SELECT meter_id FROM meters WHERE location_id IN (
    SELECT location_id FROM locations WHERE customer_id IN (
      SELECT customer_id FROM customers WHERE plan_name = 'Industrial'
    )
  )
);

external_knowledge:
1 kWh is a unit of energy equivalent to one kilowatt of power sustained for one hour; 
The rate per kWh is the cost of energy per kilowatt-hour, and it varies depending on the tariff; 
The value of the data point is converted to kWh by multiplying it by 1000 (to convert from watts to kilowatts) and dividing by 3600 (to convert from seconds to hours).

